                    <h3>Understanding the challenge:<br />What problems are we here to solve? What do we have to work with?</h3>
                    <p>I begin by asking questions and diving deep into both the businesses’ and our users' goals for the project.</p>

                    <p>As I go, I use a quadrant system where where I document:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Solvable problems - business and users' needs that we're addressing</li>
                        <li>Questions - areas for exploration, clarification and research</li>
                        <li>Quick wins and opportunities to elevate - potential solutions that spring to mind immediately, and places where we can go from just sorta solving a problem to <em>really</em> delivering a better experince</li>
                        <li>Goals and KPIs - key performance indicators - things that we should see change if we're doing the thing right.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>This becomes a living document that I share with people as the project goes. It lets me get feedback and constantly evaluate and re-evaluate whether I'm understanding the problem space and making solutions that align with everyone's goals and deliverable given the resources we have.</p>
                </div>

            </div>

        </div>
        
    </div>

</section>

