                    <h3>Whiteboarding, Sketching and Getting Feedback</h3>
                    <p>Once I understand the problem space, some ideas have usually started to bubble up about how we
                        could
                        do things better. I start on whiteboards and paper, identifying both quick wins and ideal future
                        solutions. I keep early designs loose and conceptual, because we’re looking for strategy,
                        working big to small.</p>
                    <p>By simultaneously thinking about what we can do now and what we might want later, I’m
                        able to focus on immediate impact while still keeping an eye to overall direction, the North
                        star.
                        Socializing these ideas early and often helps get buy-in and insight into what's easy, hard, and
                        unknown.</p>
                </div>

            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

</section>

